  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The ability of the SAGIT® instrument to accurately discriminate between controlled and uncontrolled patients depending on their level of disease control.</measure>
    <time_frame>2 years</time_frame>
    <description>Evaluated by the Area Under the Receiver Operating Characteristics Curve (ROC curve) characterising the separation of controlled and not controlled patients.
Disease control status will be defined according to clinical evaluation of disease control (CGE-DC), classification based upon the investigator's therapeutic decision for the management of their patients, and classification based upon international guidelines.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>The ability of the SAGIT® instrument to predict the occurrence of significant clinical event(s) and/or treatment change(s) over time.</measure>
    <time_frame>2 years</time_frame>
    <description>The relative risk of each significant clinical event according to control status (controlled vs. not controlled) as defined by SAGIT scoring algorithm will be assessed.
Significant clinical event is defined as death, stroke, onset of diabetes, onset of arthritis/onset of arthritis disability, myocardial infarction and/or diagnosis of other tumor; treatment change is defined as change in therapeutic doses, in therapeutic drug class, surgery or radiotherapy.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Define patient profiles in terms of SAGIT® characteristics (controlled vs. not controlled and treatment-naïve patients vs. currently treated vs. previously treated patients).</measure>
    <time_frame>2 years</time_frame>
    <description>The SAGIT characteristics of treatment-naïve, currently treated and previously treated patients (at baseline) patients will be described.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>The association between the SAGIT tool and patients' quality of life.</measure>
    <time_frame>2 years</time_frame>
    <description>Acromegaly Quality of Life (AcroQoL) scores will be compared between patient groups defined according to SAGIT scoring algorithm (controlled vs. not controlled). This comparison will be performed using t-tests for each available visit of the prospective population.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
